# lean-ctx configuration (ModMe)

## Paths

- **Global (active):** `~/.config/lean-ctx/config.toml` (XDG)
- **Legacy (warn only):** `~/.lean-ctx/config.toml`
- **Project overrides:** repo root `.lean-ctx.toml` (merged; project wins)
- **Schema reference:** `docs/lean-ctx/config-schema.json` — from `lean-ctx config schema`; not read at runtime

## Ensure workflow

```powershell
yarn lean-ctx:ensure              # detect + safe auto-apply missing keys
yarn lean-ctx:ensure -- -CheckOnly
yarn lean-ctx:schema:sync
yarn lean-ctx:doctor
```

Script: `scripts/ensure-lean-ctx-config.ps1` — backs up `.bak` before writes; never overwrites customized keys without `-Force`.

## ModMe preset (set only if key missing)

`compression_level=max`, `memory_profile=balanced`, `tool_profile=power`, `proxy_enabled=true`, `max_ram_percent=5`, `graph_index_max_files=15000` (global); project `.lean-ctx.toml` sets `graph_index_max_files=15000`.

Use CLI as source of truth (`lean-ctx config set`); do not hand-convert JSON schema to TOML.

## Hybrid tool mapping

See always-on [lean-ctx.mdc](./lean-ctx.mdc): `ctx_read` / `ctx_search` (MCP) + `lean-ctx -c` (shell).

